<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-11737] Add a way to disable severity in DynamicEndpointSnitch</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-11737</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I have seen in a few clusters now where severity can out weigh latency in DynamicEndpointSnitch causing issues (a node that is completely overloaded CPU wise and has super high latency will get selected for queries, even though nodes with much lower latency exist, but they have a higher severity score).  There should be a way to disable the use of severity.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12966172">CASSANDRA-11737</key>
            <summary>Add a way to disable severity in DynamicEndpointSnitch</summary>
