                            <comment id="15276554" author="JIRAUSER308715" created="Mon, 9 May 2016 16:04:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/JeremiahDJordan/cassandra/commits/CASSANDRA-11737-21&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/JeremiahDJordan/cassandra/commits/CASSANDRA-11737-21&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That merges up cleanly all the way to trunk.  Adds a -D option to disable using severity in DynamicEndpointSnitch calculations.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For the clusters where we were seeing massive latency degredation when a single node was under load applying this patch and settings the -D to disable severity brought things back to normal.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15278233" author="iamaleksey" created="Tue, 10 May 2016 15:03:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed as &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/tree/cassandra-2.1&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;11d4e73e215cfe8baa16d9d6e0a589d6a94de56b&lt;/a&gt; to 2.1 and merged with 2.2, 3.0, 3.7, and trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
